issue.title: Pin CodeQL bundle to 2.15.0
issue.body: CodeQL 2.15.1 has a few breaking changes that would require more time investment to fix. For now we will pin it to 2.15.0 to revert back to a working version.

issue.title: CodeQL 2.15.0 breaks custom queries
issue.body:
CodeQL updated to 2.15.1 which causes the following on our scans
```
  ERROR: Could not resolve type DataFlow2::BarrierGuard (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:23,44-67)

  ERROR: Class must extend or implement at least one type (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:23,7-35)
  ERROR: This predicate does not override another predicate (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:26,3-29,4)
  WARNING: Module DataFlow has been deprecated and may be removed in future (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:36,45-53)
  WARNING: Module DataFlow has been deprecated and may be removed in future (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:39,31-39)
  WARNING: Module DataFlow has been deprecated and may be removed in future (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:43,29-37)
  ERROR: This predicate does not override another predicate (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:50,3-52,4)
  WARNING: Module DataFlow has been deprecated and may be removed in future (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:60,27-35)
  WARNING: Module DataFlow has been deprecated and may be removed in future (/__w/_temp/codeql_databases/temp/external-repos/0-openenclave-security/src/static/codeql/queries/cpp/openenclave/ECall-Args-IsOutsideEnclave.ql:60,56-64)
  WARNING: Module DataFlow has been deprecated and may be removed in future (/__t/CodeQL/2.15.1/x64/codeql/qlpacks/codeql/cpp-all/0.10.1/semmle/code/cpp/dataflow/internal/tainttracking1/TaintTrackingParameter.qll:4,10-53)
```
CodeQL bundle 2.15.1 has the following packs:
```
dependencies:
  codeql/cpp-all:
    version: 0.10.1
  codeql/dataflow:
    version: 0.1.1
  codeql/ssa:
    version: 0.2.1
  codeql/tutorial:
    version: 0.2.1
  codeql/typetracking:
    version: 0.2.1
  codeql/util:
    version: 0.2.1
```

CodeQL bundle 2.15.0 has the following packs:
```
dependencies:
  codeql/cpp-all:
    version: 0.10.0
  codeql/dataflow:
    version: 0.1.0
  codeql/ssa:
    version: 0.2.0
  codeql/tutorial:
    version: 0.2.0
  codeql/typetracking:
    version: 0.2.0
  codeql/util:
    version: 0.2.0
```

Some useful links for more information on this issue:
* Changelog for [codeql/cpp-all@0.10.1](https://github.com/github/codeql/blob/3b3c03662602795a09a0984551ad4d9a2e0fd62c/cpp/ql/lib/CHANGELOG.md)
* [QL Language reference](https://codeql.github.com/docs/ql-language-reference/ql-language-specification/)

comment.body:
Please revert the name (not the values) changes back to what you had before as those were correct.

The names specifies the names of the parameters used in the openenclave-testing pipeline. The values are the parameters specified in this pipeline (i.e. lines 27-46 in this file).

What this section does is pass specific parameters from this pipeline into OpenEnclave-Testing pipeline to run, which is why the names are similar but different. The inconsistency can be fixed by changing all occurrences to be prefixed with either `WS*` or `WINDOWS_*` or something else, but that is outside the scope of this PR.
